=== HeadLines ===
Contributors: Marcelo Mesquita <marcelo.costa@cultura.gov.br>
Tags: headlines
Requires at least: 2.7
Tested up to: 2.9

Allow to reorganize the post by user's priorities beside WordPress chronological order.

== Description ==

Allow to reorganize the post by user's priorities beside WordPress chronological order.

== Installation ==

1. Upload `minc-headlines` to the `/wp-content/plugins/` directory
1. Activate the plugin through the 'Plugins' menu in WordPress
1. Open the theme file where you want to use the HeadLine
1. Load the HeadLines posts with the HL_Query (similar to WP_Query), eg.: '$headlines_loop = new HL_Query( "showposts=5&headline_category_name=headlines" );'
1. Alternatively you can use the HeadLines widget too, just drag'n drop to the sidebar

